<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="31" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 59 D
                                            95. CF 102</note>
                                        <head>
                                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by
                                                  <persName corresp="#p_BATTLELC1">Lucius D.
                                                  Battle</persName>
                                            </hi>
                                        </head>
                                        <opener>
                                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                                <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>,
                                                  <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1952-02-14">February 14,
                                                1952</date>.</dateline>
                                        </opener>
                                        <p>During a conversation on other matters, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>
                                            mentioned the proposed move of the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Headquarters from
                                            London to Paris. The Secretary said he made a very
                                            vigorous speech to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>
                                            regarding this problem and that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> was a
                                            little surprised and hard-up for answers on points which
                                            the Secretary made in which he urged the Headquarters be
                                            moved to Paris.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </body></text></TEI>